lines.line: Hello again.
Oh yes, before I forget - are you still in the adventuring business?
I am! Do you have another quest for me?
Well, I don't - but I happen to know someone who might!
Who's that then?
Well, there are these two ladies who are looking for adventurers with cats.
They called themselves 'The Ratcatchers'.
Ratcatchers, eh? Where would I find them?
They told me they generally hang about in the sewers below Varrock. I can't stand it down there, or I'd have looked into this ratcatching business myself.
I wouldn't have thought you'd have much business down in the sewers.
I've had to drag Shilop and Wilough out of there more times than I care to count, the little rascals.
I don't know which is harder, raising kids or cats.
Thank you Gertrude, I'll be sure to have a look for these ratcatchers.
Very well. Is there anything else I can do for you?
I'll be off. See you another time.
Interesting, but I'm a bit busy right now. Maybe another time.
Oh yes, before I forget I think there are some people you should meet.
The two ladies you said I could find in Varrock's sewers? Yes, you told me about them.
Oh good. You can go and see them in the sewers whenever you're not too busy. Now, is there anything else I can do for you?
Who are you?
And what do you want?
I'm Gertrude's friend. She said you two were-
Ratcatchers?
Oh yes, we know lots about ratcatching.
But why should we tell you?
These are our trade secrets, you know.
My cat and I are adventurers. If you could teach us a trick or two I bet it would come in handy!
We'll have to confer.
What do you think?
I don't think cats even do tricks.
Don't be stupid! Can we teach ratcatching?
I don't know. Seems a bit weird.
I can hear you, you know!
We'll set a task, see how it goes.
Great idea!
I already have this medal that Gertrude gave me for catching 100 rats. Will that do?
That's no good. How do we know you didn't buy it?
You could trust me?
Boo! Bring on the task!
Right, if you catch 8 ratsies with your cat...
We'll tell you what we know.
Sound fair?
I suppose so. How will you know that I've completed your task?
We'll smell your cat, of course!
Um... alright.
Great! Let's have a sniff then.
Are you alright, cat?
I'll live.
Miaoww!
Yup. Definitely a cat!
A real pongy one, too.
Go on then, go splat them ratsies!
Splat 'em! Squash 'em!
Er, will do.
Hello.
back!
splatted some ratsies?
more of 'em.
How many, er, 'ratsies' do I have to catch again?
8 ratsies. And your cat has to catch them. Any you get don't count.
Got it!
Nope!
Not even one!
Rubbish!
Boo!
Alright, no need to rub it in.
Good job puss, we really showed those rats what for.
What for what now?
Oh never mind, it's just a turn of phrase.
Speaking of turning faces, we should tell those funny-smelling humans that we're done.
Suppose so.
Miaow.
Well cat, we should tell Grimesquit and Phingspet that we're done.
They're not going to be able to sniff whether I was successful or not unless I bring my cat with me.
I splatted the ratsies for you.
Why are you talking like that?
Are you making fun of us?
Sorry, I just thought... won't happen again.
So did you splat them ratsies or what?
Er, yes, I did... catch the rats.
Haha, nice!
Splat! Splat!
Can you tell me about ratcatching now?
Ha! Seems you already know plenty!
Oh yes, you're a real ratcatching prodigy.
Reminds me of us when we were little.
I'm not sure that's a compliment...
Well, there's nothing more we can teach you.
Not much at all!
What? So we've just caught all these rats for nothing?
Isn't there anything you can teach me? I caught a lot of rats, you know...
Here, have a rat pole.
Um, thanks. What's this for?
You can stick all the ratsies your cat splats on it.
Oh. Just what I wanted.
You're welcome!
Now now, keep your shirt on.
We'll send you to Jimmy.
Ooh, yes, Jimmy will know how to help.
Where do I find this... Jimmy?
Jimmy Dazzler hangs out in Ardougne.
Ooh, and he is dazzling!
Shut up, Grimesquit!
Say hello to Jimmikins from me, won't you?
Er, sure.
Would you look at that!
At what?
It's again!
What do you want?
Can I have another rat pole please?
Here you go.
Stick the ratsies your cat splats on it!
Er... will do.
Anything else?
Where can I find Jimmy Dazzler again?
Didn't you find him in Ardougne?
He's normally in the Flying Horse Inn.
Give him a kiss from me!
I will absolutely not be doing that.
Ah, you must be. I've been expectorating you.
You... have?
I have. The Sisters Grime told me you'd be dropping in.
They said you could teach me a thing or two about ratcatching.
Well, I could, but I need a little more motivation than that.
I didn't get this far by giving out help freely to every adventurer who came my way.
Maybe I could help you out with something then?
I am an adventurer after all.
Ah, that's mincemeat to my ears!
Music?
No thank you! Your unrefined caterwauling would only draw attention.
How about I test your ratcatching mettle instead?
Oh, your hands are full. Don't worry, I'll hold onto this map until you can jettison all that rubbish.
Take a good long look at this map.
A client of mine, a merchant of some repute, is having a sorbet.
A what?
A soy - a fancy party. Don't interrupt me again.
This client of mine has a problem, a small furry one.
He'd be better off calling a doctor about that.
No, you fool! A rat problem.
So you want me to go to his place and kill some rats? That sounds easy enough.
Ah, but it's not that simple. Here's your first lesson - we ratcatchers must be discreet.
Our wealthier clients would be ruined if word got out that their fancy mansions were filled with vermin.
Oh, I see. So I have to do this covertly?
Precisely!
Now just in case, I'm going to cast a spell on you that will allow you carry out this task with some element of safety.
Are you going to cast an invisibility spell on me? That should make it easy.
Not quite. If you're spotted, this spell will teleport you a short distance away and render the last few seconds of your discoverer's memory blank.
That's really useful!
Where'd you learn that spell, anyway?
That's a trade secret, m'afraid.
Well, can you teach me?
Oh my, no. Can you imagine if all the riffraff in Ardougne got wind of this?
We already have a serious crime problem.
Oh, I see.
But there's plenty more I can teach you about ratcatching... if you complete the task I've set you.
Do you have any tips for me now?
Of course! Use a cat to catch the rats.
That's it?
Don't look a gilt horse in the mouth!
You mean a gift horse?
I'll gift you no such thing! Now go on, get out of here!
Off I go then...
Ah, you're back. Have you completed your mission?
I've lost the map you gave me. Can I have another?
Here you go, don't lose this one.
Is there anything else?
Haven't I given you the map already? I'm sure I have. I can't afford to be throwing maps around nilly willy.
What am I meant to do again?
Read the directions on the map to get to the manor. Once there, eliminate any rats you see with your cat and return to me unseen. Got it?
Got it. Thanks for the reminder.
Good, good.
I think I should have a cat big enough to catch rats with me before I go.
I don't want to go there again. I barely managed to get out the first time.
These directions are from Ardougne. It would be much easier to find the place if I left from there.
I think I'll go there some other time.
Directions to... here, actually! I'd better hold onto them until I complete Jimmy's task.
Good job, Puss, I think that just about wraps things up here.
Aw, really? I was enjoying that.
I'm a cold blooded, claw toting, hitkitty.
A callous cat.
I knew you had a dark side.
I have many dark sides.
Well, we had better get out of here. Let's do it quietly.
Ah, aren't you just the ticket?
I am?
A job well done. Confabulations!
No, the job really is done!
What?
Never mind. So you'll teach me all about ratcatching now?
Of course! If you want to learn about ratcatching, get yourself to the Rat Pits here in Ardougne.
It's a great place for training kittens. Just look at Bones here!
I think of nothing but murder all day!
He does look good at catching rats. But what about older cats?
Ah, well. My good friend Hooknosed Jack can tell you all about those.
He has the oldest cat I've ever seen.
Where do I find this... Hooknosed Jack?
He hangs around in a rather unfashionable part of Varrock. He likes a good scrap, does Jack.
I'll tell him to look out for you.
Can you tell me more about the Rat Pits?
The pits lie below this very pub.
See that ladder there? That's the way in.
What goes on in these pits then?
I'd have thought it was self-exploratory. Here, have a manual.
Here, take this, you might find it useful.
Hello! Are you Hooknosed Jack?
Depends who's asking. What do you want?
Jimmy Dazzler sent me. He said you could help train my grown cat to catch rats.
I expect he wants me to do that for free, does he?
Well, I'm an adventurer. There must be something I can do for you in return.
Forget it.
What?
I'm too busy to babysit you and your moggy.
Oh, come on.
No, really. Me and Pox have too much going on.
We've got a big job to finish today, I can't teach you how to catch rats on top of that.
Well I could be your apprentice! I've already got hands-on experience.
Oh yes? What sort of experience?
I helped the Grime Sisters catch loads of rats in the sewers, and I cleared out a whole mansion in Ardougne for Jimmy Dazzler.
I bet you did. Typical Jimmy, leaving the hard work to everyone else.
So what do you say? Can me and my cat help you out?
Oh, alright then. But you'd better not give me or Pox any trouble!
We won't!
I'd better not regret this...
Right, your first task is to clear out a warehouse south of here.
All you need to do is poison the rat holes with some bait. Can you handle that?
I think so. Will any type of poison do?
Are you daft? You need rat poison to kill rats!
If you can't mix a batch up for yourself, there's sure to be some lying around here somewhere.
Would this stuff do?
It certainly will! There's hope for you yet.
How would I mix my own rat poison?
Honestly, kids these days...
Just bring me the base ingredients, and I'll mix it up for you.
What are the ingredients then?
Get me some Kwuarm, some red spider eggs, and a vial.
Right, to poison the rats you'll need some tasty bait.
They love a bit of cheese, so pour some poison on that and then leave it in the rat holes.
Okay, can do.
Report back to me when you're done.
And no slacking!
Hey!
What?
Can you make me some rat poison?
Have you got the ingredients for me yet?
No, not yet. What do I need again?
Get some Kwuarm, Red Spider Eggs and an empty vial. Bring them to me, and I'll make a batch of rat poison for you.
Do you see that bar to the south of here? Well, behind that is the warehouse. The rats are on the first floor.
I've finished the job. Now will you teach me more about ratcatching?
You're pulling my leg!
Who, me?
Yes, you! You think I can't tell you're lying? Now get back to the warehouse and kill those rats!
Um... let me think about this one.
No! That would be stupid.
Putting random things in rat holes isn't my idea of fun.
Well that's one less rat hole. I had better finish the job off quick before they start to reproduce again.
Hmm, that should do the trick. Those rats should soon die off.
I poisoned the rats in the warehouse! Do you have time to teach me about grown cats yet?
Not right now,.
Are you serious? I've gone and done a job for you, the least you could do is say thanks.
Can't you see I'm upset?
It's my cat, Pox. She's half dead, bless her.
Oh no! What happened?
They found her at the warehouse you were working at. She must have eaten some of the rats you poisoned.
Oh no...
Can I help? I feel somewhat responsible...
That's kind of you,.
There's an apothecary here in town, he could help. Tell him that the poison was made from red spiders eggs and kwuarm. He should know what to do. Go quickly.
Putting things in poisoned rat holes isn't my idea of fun.
Hi cat!
I am the Apothecary. I brew potions. Do you need anything specific?
I need to talk to you about cats.
As I said before, I'm the apothecary not the vet.
Well, do you know anything about poisons?
Of course I do! What kind of poison do you need help with?
How about rat poisons and anti-posisons for cats?
I think I can help you with that. What happened?
Okay. Hooknosed Jack's cat, Pox, ate some rats which were poisoned with a Kwuarm and Red Spider Egg based concoction.
Not Pox! I remember when she was a kitten... hang on, I have no time for dilly dallying.
I know just the thing to help Pox out.
Great! How can I help?
I need a Bucket of Milk, some Ground Unicorn Horn, and a bit of Marrentill.
Quick, get this to Jack. If I know him, he wouldn't have sent someone else to do this if Pox wasn't seriously ill.
You need to get a Bucket of Milk and some Marrentill before we can proceed.
What are you hanging around here for? You've got the anti-poison, so go give it to Jack. Quickly!
Have you got the anti-poison?
Yes, I've got it right here.
Thank you. Thank you so much.
No worries there, I'd be sorry to see poor Pox come to harm.
Well, thanks to you, she'll live to see another day.
I have to have a word with you about the job you did in the warehouse.
I did a good job, didn't I?
The thing is, you didn't quite finish the warehouse job.
Wait, but I poisoned all the rat holes just like you said.
You did, but one rat survived... the biggest, nastiest one of the lot.
Well, I'm not scared of big, nasty rats.
I hope not, because someone's got to get rid of it, and me and Pox are out of action.
Don't worry - we're on the case.
I really underestimated you,. Best of luck.
Have you killed the King Rat yet?
Umm... no.
Look, you did me and Pox a big favour, but that's not an excuse to slack off.
How's Pox doing anyway?
Oh, she's doing alright...
Oi! You can't distract me like that. Get on with you, and get rid of that rat!
Be careful in there, cat!
Hisss!
Pfssst!
Go get that nasty rat, don't hold back!
They say you've killed the King Rat.
Just barely! I was getting worried for my cat, but we pulled through.
Your cat?
Yes! The King Rat was holed up behind a wall, so I had to send my cat in to get it.
Well, imagine that. You two must have a great bond. Perhaps I can show you a thing or two after all.
See that manhole over there? Climb down it to enter the Varrock Rat Pits.
Thank you so much! I imagine my cat will learn a lot in there.
Just you look after it.
Say, if you want to know more about the ratcatching business, you should seek out Smokin' Joe in Keldagrim. He was a skilled ratcatcher, back in the day.
Hi! What are you doing?
Isn't it obvious?
No, not really.
Bluaaghhaha! Ahem. Sorry.
I'm trying to smoke these pesky rats out. Ahem-hem-hem.
Are you alright?
I'll - ugh - I'll be fine, youngin'. My lungs just aren't up for ratcatchin' like they used to be.
Bluaaghhaha!
Ratcatching, you say?
I could help you. I'm young-ish and my lungs are doing fine so far.
That's-
Bluaaaghhaha!
-kind of you, youngin'.
What's up with your lungs anyway?
Years of blowin' smoke into rat holes, youngin'.
Oh dear. Speaking of rats...
You offered to help me out.
That's right! Me and my cat have been learning from the best of the best.
The Sisters Grime, Jimmy Dazzler, Hooknosed Jack...
Blimey, that's my old crew! How are they all?
Better now that I've helped them out, I think.
Now, how should I get rid of these rats?
That's sim-
bluaaghhaha...
simple. Take this pot, light the contents, and blow the smoke into the hole.
Er... this pot specifically?
Aye, this pot. What's wrong with it?
It's a bit... phlegmy...
You'd better make your own then. A-hem-hem.
Just take a simple pot and stick some ordinary garden weeds in it. Then light the pot and use it on a rat hole.
Great. I'll get to it.
Have you got that job done yet, youngin'?
No, not yet.
How's your cough?
Aheeh - hoo.
Better with you helpin' me out, youngin'.
Say, when the job's done, how about I show you to the Rat Pits here in Keldagrim?
That seems a fair deal. But I'd appreciate any pointers you could give me.
An extra pair of eyes or set of claws can often come in handy.
Do you have any more straightforward hints?
Bluaaaghhaha! Hurk-!
Never mind, I'll figure it out!
Hmm... this isn't working as well as I'd hoped.
Miaaaaow!
Hold on, let me equip my Catspeak Amulet so we can talk.
Hey, talk to me.
Can't you see I'm busy adventuring?
Look, I know you're having fun, but you're doing this all wrong.
Well then smarty paws, what should I be doing?
What we have here is a two cat job.
You're smoking the rats out, but the smoke clears fast enough for them to run back in before you can catch them.
I can see that for myself, thanks.
Listen, why don't you leave the rat-catching to the expert? Tell me when you're going to start the fire and I'll run and catch the rats.
Great idea. I'll get right to it.
Hey cat, you know the drill, get going!
Exterminate! Exterminate!
Sorry, I got a little carried away there.
Hey cat, great job. What an ambush!
Mua-ha-ha!
You know, you really scare me sometimes.
I got the rats.
Well good - ahem - good show.
I'd better show you our rat pits here in Keldagrim.
Great stuff. Let's go.
They're nice, but the ones they have in Port Sarim are even better.
They have rat pits in Port Sarim?
Oh yes! It's the best place to train your wily cat.
Wily cats?
Well, I suppose there's no harm tellin' you.
A-hem!
Look for 'The Face' in Port Sarim. She'll show you.
So where are the Keldagrim rat pits then?
Down the stairs to the basement of the 'Laughing Miner'. Get yourself a drink, too, you've earned it.
Um, yes?
Boss wants to talk to you. She's downstairs in the pits.
Hello, The Face said you wanted to speak with me.
Ah, we meet at last. My fellow ratcatchers tell me you're quite the talent.
Well I can't take all the credit, I've had more than a little help from my cat.
Ah, modesty. A trait seldom displayed by adventurers like yourself.
Too many more like you and I'll lose half of my business.
Why's that?
Epic poems aren't usually commissioned by the shy and retiring.
Smokin' Joe said that you know lots about training wily cats.
I do indeed. In fact, that's why I wanted to talk to you.
So you'll show me how to turn my cat into a wily cat?
Ah, ah, ah - not so fast.
Let me guess... you want me to catch some rats for you first?
Bingo.
Alright then, what's the job?
Nothing too difficult. Just rid the port of every single rat... at once.
At once?!
Yep. I expect to see all the rats in Port Sarim dead in one, decisive action.
Are you serious?
Deadly!
So why do you want all the rats wiped out at once?
I want to write a new poem.
About me?! How flattering.
No, silly. A poem about the art of ratcatching.
Poetry might be my bread and butter, but catching rats is my real passion.
Couldn't you just use some 'creative license' instead?
Not to disappoint you, but this task might be beyond my capabilities...
Don't be so hard on yourself!
Besides, it's not difficult. I myself performed the very same feat just a few years ago.
You did? How?
Ha! Nice try. You'll have to figure that out for yourself.
It was worth a shot...
Any luck killing all the rats yet?
What do I have to do again?
Kill all the rats in Port Sarim in one, swift action.
Right. I'd better figure out how I'm going to do that...
Oh. It's you again.
Have you spoken with the boss yet?
Yes. Actually, I wanted to ask you about the task she gave me...
Stop right there. You'll get not hints out of me.
You know, you're very pretty...
Ha! That's a good one.
I hope you're better at ratcatching than lying.
That's a powerful-looking cat you have there.
Bellemorde? Beautiful, isn't she?
Er... yes.
I've had her since she was a kitten. Felkrash trained her for me.
Oh really? Does she know any cool tricks?
Oh yes! There was this one time she helped Felkrash wipe out all the rats in town by -
Hiss!
Oh, I see. Nice try, but you'll have to be cleverer than that.
Almost had it...
I just don't think Felkrash was that impressive.
What?
All the other ratcatchers I've met had loads of tricks to show me.
In comparison, Felkrash was just... disappointing.
How dare you! Felkrash is the greatest ratcatcher Gielinor's ever seen!
Oh yeah? What's the most impressive thing she's done then?
I'll have you know she once killed all the rats in Port Sarim with just one attack!
I don't know. That just sounds like one of her stories.
It's true! I saw it happen. She used a magic flute to charm the rats into the sea!
Wait... I uh, I shouldn't have said that.
Don't worry, I won't tell Felkrash you snitched.
You'd better not!
They charm snakes over in Pollnivneach... maybe they charm rats, too?
Oh it's you again.
Felkrash told me of the task she set you.
Oh, er, really?
I shouldn't have told you that story. Shame on you for coaxing it out of me.
If it makes you feel better, I lie to a lot of people.
I think I know how to carry out your task.
Oh yes? Has The Face been telling tales again?
Oh no, she didn't say a word.
Really, she didn't.
I want to talk to you about animal charming.
Can you help me learn how to charm animals?
That depends. How much are you willing to pay?
I'm not paying you again!
Listen, do you know someone called Felkrash?
Felkrash the Bard? Pah!
I taught her all she knows about animal charming, and then she used my knowledge to kill!
What's wrong with killing rats? That is her job, after all.
Music should never be used to kill.
When I first met Felkrash we sang about love, not war.
Oh, things were a lot better in those days.
So there's nothing I could do to get you teach me how to charm rats?
Absolutely nothing.
What if I offered you a drink?
I'd say thank you very much and take it.
But would you teach me?
That might depend on how the drink tasted.
So what's your favourite drink then?
Beer, just plain old beer.
Ahh, that hit the spot.
So will you teach me now?
Nope.
But... but...
Sorry!
I don't have any beer on me.
That's too bad!
What if I offered you some food?
I'd say I wasn't hungry.
What if I offered you some money?
Now we're talking.
How much money are we talking about?
I'll teach you for coins.
I don't have that much money!
You're a resourceful looking adventurer. I'm sure you'll figure something out.
I'll go get more money...
I'll be waiting!
What if I offered you 50 coins?
Yes... that sounds fair...
It's not that difficult. Here, take these.
Study the sheet music carefully. Playing it on the flute will draw rats to you like flies to a bucket of camel dung.
Forget about it. I don't care that much.
What? I'm offering something invaluable, and you'll quibble over a couple of coins?
No, I'm done here.
Good luck finding someone else to help...
I'll do it for half the price.
I'll do it for quarter the price.
I'll...
You'll what?
An eighth?
No!
I'll give you no more than 100 coins.
Deal!
What if I said I'd kill you?
If you killed me, you'd never learn my technique.
You've got me there...
I've lost some of the gear you gave me.
What do you need?
I've lost the flute.
I've lost the music.
I need a new flute and some music.
There you go. Now if you don't mind, I'm busy performing.
Yes?
How do I charm rats again?
Do you remember that flute I gave you?
Yes.
And the music?
Well, play the music that's on the sheet and that should do the trick.
Thanks!
I don't think I should play that tune here.
That was an amazing performance! I've only seen one like it... as you know.
Don't worry, Felkrash has no idea how I figured it out.
And it had better stay that way!
I don't want to play that tune again - I'll have a pack of rats chasing after me!
Ha! I did it. Did you see?
I did indeed! A performance for the ages.
Now that you're a real ratcatcher, I'd be happy to train that cat of yours.
Can you train my cat to be a wily cat?
I can only train overgrown cats into wily cats.
A heroic cat like yours needs a heroic name, don't you think?
Shall we rename it?
Hey, you finally got around to naming me.
Sorry I took so long, it took a while to come up with a name for you.

characters.name: Ali the Snake Charmer
characters.description: Middle-aged male, Middle Eastern accent, calm and mysterious tone with a hint of greed, a snake charmer who speaks in a measured, musical cadence befitting someone who manipulates creatures through melody.

characters.name: Apothecary
characters.description: Older male, British accent, professional and knowledgeable tone, an experienced potion brewer in Varrock who speaks with the confidence of someone who has practiced his craft for decades.

characters.name: Bellemorde
characters.description: Female cat, raspy and gruff voice, unkempt and street-wise personality, a scrappy feline companion with a no-nonsense attitude befitting a seasoned rat-catcher's pet.

characters.name: Bones
characters.description: Male cat, energetic and slightly unhinged voice, playful yet murderous personality, a kitten who thinks of nothing but hunting and has an unsettling enthusiasm for violence.

characters.name: Cat
characters.description: Neutral cat voice, dry and sardonic tone with dark humor, an intelligent feline companion who speaks with surprising wit and occasionally reveals a sinister side.

characters.name: Felkrash
characters.description: Middle-aged female, British accent, enigmatic and confident tone with poetic flair, a mysterious bard and legendary ratcatcher who carries herself with quiet authority.

characters.name: Gertrude
characters.description: Middle-aged female, British accent, warm but busy tone, a practical housewife and mother of four who loves cats and speaks with the patience of someone accustomed to managing chaos.

characters.name: Grimesquit
characters.description: Adult female, British accent, eccentric and slightly unhinged tone, one of the Grime Sisters who lives in the sewers and speaks with manic enthusiasm about catching rats.

characters.name: Hooknosed Jack
characters.description: Middle-aged male, working-class British accent, gruff and no-nonsense tone, a tough ratcatcher from Varrock who deeply cares for his cat Pox despite his rough exterior.

characters.name: Jimmy Dazzler
characters.description: Adult male, upper-class British accent, theatrical and pompous tone with frequent malapropisms, a wealthy exterminator who fancies himself sophisticated but consistently misuses words.

characters.name: King rat
characters.description: Male rat voice, squeaky and defiant tone with false bravado, the last surviving rat in the warehouse who hisses and snarls with desperate aggression.

characters.name: Phingspet
characters.description: Adult female, British accent, eccentric and slightly manic tone, one of the Grime Sisters who lives in the sewers and speaks with childlike excitement about hunting rats.

characters.name: Smokin' Joe
characters.description: Elderly male dwarf, Scottish accent, wheezy and gravelly voice interrupted by constant coughing, a retired ratcatcher whose lungs are ruined from years of smoking out rat holes.

characters.name: The Face
characters.description: Adult female, British accent, cold and dismissive tone that softens slightly after gaining respect, a gatekeeper at the Port Sarim Rat Pits who was once beautiful but is now weathered.
